<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Endemic to 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Querétaro">Queretaro</normalizedToken>
in Mexico, where it grows in dry pine and oak woodland at 2200 m on rocky limestone soil.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
MEXICO. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Querétaro">Queretaro</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
: type collection.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The distinct 3-lobed, discolorous leaves, very long peduncles, acuminate, aristate sepals with prominent scarious margins and the reddish-purple pubescent corolla mark out this species. There is a strong, probably superficial, resemblance to 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spruceana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea spruceana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the leaf shape and colouring, inflorescence structure and sepal shape but the shortly pubescent indumentum is very different from the pilose inflorescence of 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spruceana">I. spruceana</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
The placement of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="calcicola">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. calcicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is uncertain and its inclusion here is based on its similarity with 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spruceana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. spruceana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
